# Testing Conventions

## Unit Tests (Vitest + React Testing Library)

- Colocate test files next to source: `Button.test.tsx` alongside `Button.tsx`.
- Import from `@testing-library/react` and use `screen` for queries:

```tsx
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/react";
import { Button } from "./Button";

test("renders button text", () => {
  render(<Button>Click me</Button>);
  expect(screen.getByRole("button", { name: /click me/i })).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

- Prefer `getByRole` over `getByTestId` — query the way a user would.
- Use `userEvent` over `fireEvent` for realistic interaction simulation:

```tsx
import userEvent from "@testing-library/user-event";

test("handles click", async () => {
  const user = userEvent.setup();
  render(<Button onClick={handleClick}>Save</Button>);
  await user.click(screen.getByRole("button", { name: /save/i }));
});
```

- Test behavior and outcomes, not implementation details (avoid testing state values or internal methods directly).

## E2E Tests (Playwright)

- Place E2E tests in the `e2e/` directory.
- Use locators (`page.getByRole`, `page.getByText`) over CSS selectors.
- Name test files descriptively: `e2e/contact-form.spec.ts`.
